Thunder Twim	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES			PRECLASSLEVELMAX:1,TYPE.Base=1															PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:RegionDwarfGold,1],[PREVARGTEQ:RegionDwarfShield,1]				DESC:You receive a +2 bonus on all Charisma based checks. You have a twin brother or sister (fraternal or identical). You may detect the direction of your twim if he or she is alive, on the same plane, and you succeed at an Intuit Direction check against DC 15 (or a Wisdom check if you do not have the skill). A failure on this check gives no information. You may retry once per round as a standard action. Special: You may only take this feat as a 1st-level character.													BONUS:SKILL|TYPE.Charisma|2				SOURCEPAGE:FRCS30					
Treetopper	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES																		PREMULT:1,[PREREGION:Aglarond,Chondalwood,High Forest],[PREVARGTEQ:RegionHalflingGhostwise,1],[PREVARGTEQ:RegionElfWild,1],[PREVARGTEQ:RegionElfWood,1]				DESC:You get a +2 bonus on all Climb checks. You do not lose your dexterity bonus to Armor Class or give your character a +2 bonus when you are attacked while climbing.													BONUS:SKILL|Climb|2				SOURCEPAGE:FRCS30					
Twin Spell	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Metamagic	VISIBLE:YES				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Metamagic																		DESC:Casting a spell altered by this feat causes the spell to take effecttwice on the target, as if you were simultaneously casting the same spell two times on the same location or target. Any variables in the spell (such as targets, shaping an area, and so on) apply to both of the resulting spell. The target suffers all the effects of both spells individually and receives a saving throw for each. In some cases, failure of both of the target's saving throws results in redundant effects, sucg as a twinned charm person (see Combining Magical Effects, page 153 of the Player's Handbook), altought any ally or of the target would have to succeed at two dispel attempts in order to free the target from the charm. As with other metamagic feats, twinning a spell does not affect its vulnerability to counterspelling (for example, using a untwinned frotm of the spell doen's negate just half of the twinned spell). A twinned spell uses up a spell slot four levels higher than the spell's actual level.						BONUS:WEAPONPROF=%LIST|CRITRANGEDOUBLE|1|TYPE=NonStackingCrit	ADDSPELLLEVEL:4										SOURCEPAGE:FRCS30					
Twin Sword Style	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fighter	VISIBLE:YES				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Two-Weapon Fighting														PREMULT:1,[PREREGION:Sembia,Waterdeep],[PREVARGTEQ:RegionElfDrow,1]				DESC:When fighting with two swords (dagger, longsword, rapier, scimitar or short sword, in any combination) you can design a melee opponent during your action and receive +2 armor bonus toi your Armor Class against attacks from that opponent. This armor bonus stacks with the armor bonus from armor and shield. You can select a new melee opponent on any action. A condition that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Armor Ckass (if any) also makes you lose this bonus. The benefits of this feats apply only if you are proficient with the weapons you are using.																	SOURCEPAGE:FRCS30					
																																															
